description:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are a General Surgical ward that predominantly cares for non-elective surgical patients. You will be working within an extended MDT comprised of Surgeons, Therapists, Nurses, Health Care Support Workers and Admin staff in a fast paced, dynamic environment. You will be expected to deliver evidence based high quality care to all patients.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Flexible working patterns considered for all nursing applicants! &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we look for:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We are looking for enthusiastic and dynamic nurses who are keen to expand their knowledge and skills within a surgical setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What we Offer:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We provide an extended induction period during which you receive support from a senior nurse, training from the therapy department and exposure to the patient journey within the trust.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We will provide the opportunities for you to develop skills essential for career progression. These skills include training in the following areas: PCA, TPN, parenteral feeds, syringe drivers and End of Life Pathways, stoma management and more.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;We offer a 12 month preceptorship programme for all our newly qualified health care professionals to support your transition into the working world. This provides a structured progression from student to employee allowing you to develop your skills as required by the Trust and governing bodies and gives you the opportunity to attend study days, training sessions and to complete an in house Service Improvement project.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you need to relocate to take up this role? For candidates who need to move to the local area to take up this opportunity to work with us, the trust may provide single occupancy accommodation in Winchester for your first 3 months of joining. This is to allow you to settle into your new role as well as the local area whilst making longer term accommodation arrangements. For newly qualified nurses, the Trust will pay your first year NMC fees!&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your life outside HHFT is important and the Trust are happy to consider applications with flexible working patterns that cater to individual requirements; this can be discussed at interview.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the trust: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The vision at Hampshire Hospitals NHS Foundation Trust is to provide outstanding care for every patient. We serve a population of nearly 600,000 people across Hampshire and West Berkshire as well as some people who access our specialist services from across the country.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Created in January 2012 the Foundation Trust prioritises the provision of exceptional, compassionate, care delivered by the valued staff working in a culture of collaboration and mutual respect. HHFT employs circa 6,000 people and had a turnover of £382m in 17/18&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Four core values (CARE) Compassion, Accountability, Respect and Encourage. These are in place to support of four clear objectives, provide outstanding care of patients, empowering all members of staff, sustainable growth and innovating for the future.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; #AspiringToBeTheBest &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Only a few vacancies remaining so if you are interested please contact us.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Barbara Vieira – Senior Sister 0196285022&lt;/p&gt;
